parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rust and corrosion of brake rotors can lead to poor braking performance, increased stopping distances, and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: Brake rotors rusted to the point of compression
poor braking performance
increased stopping distances
grinding or screeching noise when applying the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the wheel cylinder can cause brake fluid leakage, leading to a loss of braking power and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: Brake fluid leakage
spongy brake pedal
reduced braking performance
grinding or screeching noise when applying the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Axle failure can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, and can also result in costly repairs.
symptoms: Vibrations or shaking while driving
loud clunking or grinding noises
difficulty steering
uneven tire wear
failure to accelerate or decelerate properly.

symptoms: Vibrations or shaking while driving

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rear seat belts may not provide adequate protection for senior citizens wearing winter coats, potentially increasing the risk of injury in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The rear seat belts are too short to accommodate senior citizens wearing winter coats
making it difficult or impossible to wear the seatbelt comfortably and securely.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An inaccurate fuel gauge can lead to unexpected fuel depletion, causing the vehicle to run out of fuel and potentially leaving occupants stranded.
symptoms: The fuel gauge does not provide an accurate reading
making it difficult for drivers to determine when to refuel.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Malfunctioning Front Passenger Motorized Shoulder Belt
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning front passenger motorized shoulder belt may not provide adequate protection in the event of an accident, potentially increasing the risk of injury.
symptoms: The front passenger motorized shoulder belt does not lock properly

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An inaccurate fuel gauge can cause the vehicle to run out of fuel unexpectedly, leading to stranded occupants and potential safety risks.
symptoms: The fuel gauge does not provide an accurate reading
the fuel gauge fluctuates erratically
the fuel gauge sticks or remains on a specific level.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A failing fuel pump can cause the vehicle to stall without warning, increasing the risk of accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls without warning
the engine sputters or hesitates before stalling
the fuel pump makes a loud whining or grinding noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning motorized shoulder belt can compromise the safety of the front passenger in the event of an accident, increasing the risk of injury.
symptoms: The motorized shoulder belt does not lock or retract properly
the belt makes a loud noise or vibrates excessively
the belt does not adjust to the correct position.
